b'In collaboration with the Embassy of Honduras in the U.S. and the Honduran Consular Network, we operated a relief flight transporting hundreds of boxes filled with household necessities and personal essentials, donated by local organizations and the Honduran community in Florida. The flight touched down in Honduras on Friday, Nov. 20, days after recent devastating storms hit, helping families in need across the affected regions. #SpiritStrong'

b'This week we presented the @NSUMDCollege with a donation of $5,000 for Park Genome Analysis software used in critical breast cancer research. The equipment is used to analyze mutations in breast cancer cell lines where it is resistive to treatments, especially among the African American population. We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to offer our ongoing support in the fight against breast cancer and will continue to support research efforts this Breast Cancer Awareness Month and beyond. #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth #SpiritStrong'
